The paper discusses lattice reduction techniques for lattice Gaussian sampling, which is a problem in coding, decoding, and cryptography. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses Markov Chain Monte Carlo methods, which are commonly used in the Data Structures (cs.DS) and Statistical Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents simulation results based on MIMO detection, which suggests that it may also belong to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
